# ChatKings backend environment template
#
# HOW TO USE
# 1) Copy this file to `.env` (local shell usage) or provide the same keys in your host
#    environment (Dokploy app env, CI secrets, etc.).
# 2) Never commit your real `.env` file.
# 3) Start the API from this folder:
#      dotnet run
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# LOCAL DEVELOPMENT (recommended default)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Use SQLite to keep local setup fast and simple.
#
# Required:
ASPNETCORE_ENVIRONMENT=Development
DatabaseProvider=Sqlite
ConnectionStrings__DefaultConnection=Data Source=ChatKings.db
#
# Optional:
# - Override API bind URL/port (otherwise launch profile/default is used):
# ASPNETCORE_URLS=http://localhost:5166
#
# Notes:
# - SQLite DB file (`ChatKings.db`) is created/updated by EF migrations at startup.
# - This mode supports easy local template DB editing.
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# PRODUCTION (PostgreSQL)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Switch provider and point the app at your Postgres instance.
#
# Required:
# ASPNETCORE_ENVIRONMENT=Production
# DatabaseProvider=Postgres
# ConnectionStrings__DefaultConnection=Host=<db-host>;Port=5432;Database=<db-name>;Username=<db-user>;Password=<db-password>;SSL Mode=Require;Trust Server Certificate=true
#
# Optional (depends on hosting/proxy):
# - If your platform sets PORT automatically (Dokploy/Railpack commonly does),
#   you can usually omit ASPNETCORE_URLS.
# - If you need explicit bind:
# ASPNETCORE_URLS=http://0.0.0.0:3000
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# QUICK CHECKLIST
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# - Local dev + SQLite:
#   - ASPNETCORE_ENVIRONMENT=Development
#   - DatabaseProvider=Sqlite
#   - ConnectionStrings__DefaultConnection points to local file
#
# - Production + Postgres:
#   - ASPNETCORE_ENVIRONMENT=Production
#   - DatabaseProvider=Postgres
#   - ConnectionStrings__DefaultConnection points to Postgres
#   - Ensure DB is reachable from app runtime network
